World War I
Documentaries
The World at War (1974), a 26-part Thames Television series that covers most aspects of World War II from many points of view. It includes interviews with many key figures including Karl D&lt;U+00F6&gt;nitz, Albert Speer, and Anthony Eden.
Battlefield (documentary series), a television documentary series initially issued in 1994&lt;U+2013&gt;1995 that explores many of the most important battles fought during the Second World War.
